        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Area</strong> 5-foot cube or 5-foot burst</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Water blasts upward, coming out of the ground, rising from a pool, or even manifesting from thin air. Any creatures in the area take 2d4 bludgeoning damage, with a basic Reflex saving throw.</p>\n<p>You can change this spell's area to a 5-foot burst, provided you center the burst in a body of water. This body of water can be as small as a pond or creek, but not as small as a puddle or bathtub.</p>\n<p>A creature that critically fails its save is disoriented by the explosion of water, becoming @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Off-Guard] until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> The damage increases by 1d4.</p>"
